m%2Famazon-rto-return-to-office-policy-news-updates-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emandatory%20for%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20show%20up%20to%20an%20office%20three%20times%20a%20week%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoldman-sachs-return-to-office-mandate-fuels-remote-work-reckoning-2023-8%23%3A~%3Atext%3DGoldman%2520Sachs%2520just%2520upped%2520the%2Cto%2520three%2520days%2520a%2520week.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoldman%20Sachs%20is%20pressuring%20staff%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20return%20full-time%2C%20and%20Meta%20has%20said%20employees%20might%20lose%20their%20jobs%20if%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-rto-policy-updates-stricter-mandate-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edon't%20turn%20up%20to%20the%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%20three%20days%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECEOs%20have%20been%20citing%20vague%20reasons%20for%20the%20shift.%20Meta%20boss%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20said%20early-career%20engineers%20tend%20to%20perform%20better%20when%20in%20the%20office%20three%20days%20a%20week%2C%20citing%20internal%20%26quot%3Bperformance%20data%26quot%3B%20that%20the%20firm%20has%20not%20made%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Amazon's%20Andy%20Jassy%20described%20the%20company's%20push%20to%20get%20workers%20back%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bjudgment%26quot%3B%20call%20based%20on%20internal%20leadership%20conversations%20and%20conversations%20with%2060%20to%2080%20other%20CEOs.%20He%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-andy-jassy-no-data-return-to-office-rto-aws-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eavoided%20questions%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20what%20data%20the%20decision%20was%20based%20on%20during%20an%20internal%20fireside%20chat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20are%20they%20right%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20CEO%20case%20against%20working%20from%20home%20forever%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20early%20studies%20suggested%20that%20working%20from%20home%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-wfh-productivity-impact-no-consensus-goldman-sachs-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%20minimal%20or%20even%20positive%20impact%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hbs.edu%2Fris%2FPublication%2520Files%2FWork%2520from%2520Anywhere_forthcoming%2520SMJ_ee8cc7c5-c90e-4ad9-a1f4-47309d693a5c.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efrom%20Harvard%20Business%20School%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20finding%20that%20it%20boosted%20productivity%20by%204.4%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20recent%20studies%20cast%20doubt%20on%20these%20early%20analyses%2C%20finding%20that%20workers%20are%20more%20distractible%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.journals.uchicago.edu%2Fdoi%2F10.1086%2F721803%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EA%20University%20of%20Chicago%20study%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20published%20February%2C%20which%20collected%20data%20from%20over%2010%2C000%20skilled%20professionals%20at%20an%20Indian%20IT%20company%20during%20the%20height%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20found%20that%20worker%20productivity%20decreased%208%25%20to%2019%25%20amongst%20staff%20working%20from%20home%2C%20even%20as%20the%20number%20of%20hours%20worked%20increased.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20found%20a%20dramatic%20decline%20in%20productivity%2C%20not%20just%20immediately%20when%20the%20pandemic%20hit%2C%20but%20throughout%20the%20entire%20period%2C%26quot%3B%20Gibbs%2C%20one%20of%20the%20authors%20of%20the%20study%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20says%20employee%20%26quot%3Bfocus%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20amount%20of%20time%20they%20spent%20per%20day%20working%20uninterrupted%2C%20fell%20dramatically%2C%20despite%20both%20the%20company%20and%20its%20employees%20being%20ideally%20suited%20to%20make%20the%20adjustment%20to%20home%20working%20in%20terms%20of%20capabilities%20and%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fworking_papers%2Fw31515%2Fw31515.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAnother%20study%20published%20in%20July%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20National%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Research%20similarly%20found%20that%20the%20productivity%20of%20workers%20randomly%20assigned%20to%20work%20from%20home%20was%2018%25%20lower%20than%20their%20in-office%20counterparts.%20The%20study%20assessed%20around%20200%20data-entry%20workers%20in%20the%20Indian%20city%20of%20Chennai.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20did%20find%20there%20was%20an%20increase%20in%20idle%20time%20and%20a%20greater%20risk%20of%20distraction%2C%26quot%3B%20David%20Atkin%2C%20one%20of%20the%20study's%20authors%20and%20a%20professor%20of%20economics%20at%20MIT%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20found%20was%20that%20the%20people%20who%20were%20most%20likely%20to%20say%20they'd%20like%20to%20work%20from%20home%20were%20the%20people%20who%2C%20when%20they%20worked%20from%20home%20compared%20to%20the%20office%2C%20were%20even%20less%20productive%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20studies%20also%20suggested%20working%20from%20home%20made%20collaboration%20and%20communication%20more%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOften%20some%20of%20the%20most%20innovative%20interactions%20between%20people%20come%20when%20you're%20at%20the%20water%20cooler%2C%20hanging%20out%20in%20the%20office%2C%20or%20bumping%20into%20each%20other%20in%20the%20lunch%20line%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20David%20Atkin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBut%2C%20but%2C%20but%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-office-mandates-restore-ceo-power-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebosses%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20see%20face%20time%20as%20a%20stand-in%20for%20productivity%20have%20cited%20many%20of%20the%20above%20arguments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20pandemic%20wrought%20such%20a%20dramatic%20change%20on%20our%20working%20lives%20that%20even%20the%20experts%20agree%20there's%20no%20going%20back%2C%20and%20a%20full%20reversion%20might%20damage%20businesses%20in%20other%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEmployees%20really%20care%20about%20flexibility%2C%20so%20return-to-office%20mandates%20come%20across%20as%20top-down%20and%20insensitive%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Raj%20Choudhury%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Harvard%20Business%20School.%20A%20company's%20lack%20of%20flexible%20working%20will%20also%20make%20it%20harder%20to%20attract%20talent%2C%20he%20added%2C%20especially%20diverse%20talent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20may%20have%20rearranged%20their%20lives%20quite%20drastically%20around%20the%20ability%20to%20work%20from%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20Atkin.%20%26quot%3BYou%20could%20imagine%20there%20being%20a%20lot%20of%20resistance%20to%20changing%20that.%20It's%20often%20very%20senior%20people%20who%20have%20made%20these%20changes%20to%20their%20lives%2C%20not%20typically%2025-year-olds%20just%20arriving%20at%20the%20company.%20These%20are%20the%20people%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20bargaining%20power.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fbusiness%2F2023%2F05%2F23%2Fpost-poll-remote-work-hybrid-future%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epoll%20this%20year%20from%20The%20Washington%20Post%20and%20Ipsos%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20more%20than%20half%20of%20US%20workers%20who%20are%20fully%20remote%20would%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-remote-workers-would-take-pay-cut-to-keep-wfh-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewilling%20to%20take%20a%20pay%20cut%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20rather%20than%20return%20to%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20concept%20of%20productivity%20itself%20is%20also%20hazy%2C%20and%20could%20be%20influenced%20by%20how%20helpful%20a%20company%20was%20when%20workers%20went%20remote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BProductivity%20in%20one%20company%20is%20not%20comparable%20to%20the%20productivity%20measurement%20in%20a%20different%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20Choudhury%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20results%20might%20depend%20on%20a%20firm's%20management%20practices%20to%20support%20hybrid%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20compare%20productivity%20or%20just%20look%20at%20productivity%20without%20also%20looking%20at%20what%20kinds%20of%20hybrid%20arrangements%20are%20in%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere'll%20be%20good%20hybrid%20and%20terrible%20hybrid.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20remote%20work%20genie%20is%20out%20of%20the%20bottle%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EInfluential%20remote%20work%20researchers%2C%20including%20Stanford%20researcher%20Nicholas%20Bloom%2C%20have%20been%20backing%20a%20flexible%2C%20hybrid%20approach%20as%20the%20way%20forward.%20Bloom%20previously%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F4-reasons-remote-work-will-survive-recession-stanfords-nick-bloom-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EInsider%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20well-organized%20hybrid%20work%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bwin-win%26quot%3B%20for%20companies%20and%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20else%20Insider%20spoke%20to%20agreed%2C%20though%20some%20said%20even%20hybrid%20was%20likely%20less%20productive%20than%20being%20fully%20in%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20definitely%20think%20that%20five%20years%20down%20the%20line%20hybrid%20will%20be%20the%20default%2C%26quot%3B%20Choudhury%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe'll%20probably%20not%20even%20debate%20that%20anymore.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20few%20high-profile%20examples%20of%20return-to-office%20mandates%20had%20been%20overplayed%20in%20the%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reality%20on%20the%20ground%20is%20that%20WFH%20has%20been%20very%20stable%20for%20at%20least%20a%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jose%20Maria%20Barrero%2C%20an%20economist%20and%20cofounder%20of%20WFH%20Research%2C%20which%20tracks%20US%20working-from-home%20levels.%20%26quot%3BMy%20guess%20is%20most%20employees%20at%20most%20of%20those%20companies%20have%20been%20de-facto%20in%20a%20hybrid%20mode%20for%20a%20while%2C%20and%20companies%20are%20mostly%20just%20formalizing%20that%20reality.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-back-to-the-office-what-the-data-really-says-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693726201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e7428052bc2d00199108c1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-back-to-the-office-what-the-data-really-says-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bosses%20such%20as%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20are%20telling%20employees%20to%20come%20back%20to%20the%20office%2C%20often%20citing%20vague%20reasons.%20Here's%20what%20top%20WFH%20researchers%20say.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tcarter%40insider.com%20(Tom%20Carter%2CBeatrice%20Nolan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A25%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-back-to-the-office-what-the-data-really-says-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22DYK%20Denzel's%20stardom%20was%20long%20predicted%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693726200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103322583%2Cimgsize-100418.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fhollywood%2Fnews%2Fhollywood-trivia-did-you-know-equaliser-3-star-denzel-washingtons-stardom-was-predicted-long-before-he-became-an-actor%2Farticleshow%2F103322617.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F103322617.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EDenzel%20Washington%20migh