my%20grandparents%20in%20Jaipur%20during%20May%2C%20summers%20weren%E2%80%99t%20something%20we%20would%20dread.%20Of%20course%2C%20we%E2%80%99d%20stay%20indoors%20between%2011%20am%20and%203%20pm%20%E2%80%94%20when%20it%20was%20very%20hot%20%E2%80%94%20but%20by%20the%20evening%2C%20the%20temperature%20would%20drop%20and%20it%20would%20be%20pleasantly%20cool%2C%20enough%20for%20us%20to%20sleep%20on%20the%20terrace%20at%20night.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20no%20longer%20have%20those%20spaces%20that%20helped%20keep%20the%20city%20cool.%20Jaipur%20has%20changed%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20for%20the%20better%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20opines.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaipur%20is%20only%20one%20among%20the%20several%20Indian%20cities%20facing%20rising%20incidents%20of%20extreme%20heat%20and%20water%20scarcity.%20Meanwhile%2C%20coastal%20cities%20like%20Kochi%20and%20Mumbai%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F236067%2Fgurgaon-gurugram-urban-flooding-rains-monsoon-ghata-lake-bunds-dams-disappear-environment-ang136%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estruggling%20with%20urban%20flooding%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Frequent%20heat%20waves%20and%20urban%20heat%20islands%20trap%20heat%20in%20neighbourhoods%2C%20giving%20residents%20little%20relief%2C%20even%20at%20night.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Furban-flooding-1693380097.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ayyankali%20workers%20preparing%20the%20land%20to%20plant%20saplings%5Cn%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Furban-flooding-1693380097.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Furban-flooding-1693380097-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Furban-flooding-1693380097-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Furban-flooding-1693380097-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Furban-flooding-1693380097-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-328525%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ECoastal%20cities%20like%20Kochi%20and%20Mumbai%20are%20struggling%20with%20urban%20flooding.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHeat%20impacts%20vulnerable%20communities%20the%20most%20due%20to%20the%20usage%20of%20unsuitable%20housing%20material%20such%20as%20tin%20sheets%20and%20lack%20of%20green%20cover.%20In%20Mumbai%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fmumbai-news%2Fmumbai-slums-are-6-degrees-celsius-warmer-than-neighbouring-housing-societies-in-october-study%2Fstory-wo22fMA4bIUjzvV5OIdamN.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslums%20in%20Dharavi%20are%20almost%206%20degrees%20hotter%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20the%20better-shaded%20and%20more%20affluent%20neighbouring%20locality%20of%20Matunga.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20scenario%2C%20working%20with%20low-income%20neighbourhoods%20at%20the%20intersection%20of%20high%20vulnerability%20to%20heat%20and%20flooding%20has%20become%20imperative.%20With%20this%20in%20mind%2C%20The%20World%20Resources%20Institute%20(WRI)%20India%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1838002%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epiloting%20different%20Nature-based%20solutions%20(NbS)%3C%2Fa%3E%20aimed%20at%20making%20communities%20more%20resilient%20to%20climate%20change.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENbS%20interventions%20not%20only%20improve%20urban%20environmental%20ecosystems%2C%20but%20also%20offer%20social%20and%20economic%20benefits%20to%20communities%20by%20creating%20healthy%20spaces%20for%20recreation%2C%20and%20by%20opening%20up%20opportunities%20for%20skilling%20up%20and%20livelihood%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhy%20are%20low-income%20groups%20so%20much%20more%20vulnerable%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Pramila%20%E2%80%94%20who%20is%20a%20community%20organiser%20and%20advisor%20at%20SIDART%2C%20an%20organisation%20that%20works%20for%20the%20upliftment%20of%20women%20and%20children%20%E2%80%94%20says%20that%20water%20scarcity%20is%20also%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20challenges%20of%20the%20city%2C%20and%20flooding%20during%20monsoons%20has%20now%20become%20extremely%20common.%20%E2%80%9CUrbanisation%20has%20impacted%20natural%20biodiversity%2C%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20forests%20and%20hills%20being%20cut%20down%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20rising%20fluctuations%20and%20climatic%20changes%20affect%20low-income%20groups%20due%20to%20a%20combination%20of%20socio-economic%20and%20demographic%20factors.%20During%20the%202005%20Mumbai%20floods%2C%20over%20a%20million%20slum%20residents%20were%20stranded.%20These%20are%20the%20neighbourhoods%20that%20often%20lack%20access%20to%20basic%20services%20and%20amenities%20like%20potable%20water%2C%20energy%2C%20sanitation.%20For%20instance%2C%2084.9%25%20of%20Mumbai%E2%80%99s%20M-East%20ward%20population%20lives%20in%20slums%2C%20and%20only%2053.6%25%20of%20these%20households%20have%20access%20to%20water%20on%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20840px)%20100vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fdharavi-1693381664.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fdharavi-1693381664.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fdharavi-1693381664-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fdharavi-1693381664-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fdharavi-1693381664-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fdharavi-1693381664-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-328543%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20slums%20in%20Dharavi%20are%20almost%206%20degrees%20hotter%20than%20the%20better-shaded%20and%20more%20affluent%20neighbouring%20locality%20of%20Matunga.%C2%A0%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20there%20are%20the%20political%20factors%2C%20including%20the%20ability%20of%20these%20communities%20to%20participate%20in%20governance%20processes%2C%20raise%20their%20concerns%20and%20have%20them%20addressed.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F255808%2Fwest-bengal-kolkata-anindita-majumdar-equidiversity-foundation-women-representation-in-rural-politics-india-gender-based-violence-disabilities-women-empowerment-div200%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVulnerable%20communities%20are%20not%20involved%20in%20%3Cem%3Esabha%3C%2Fem%3E%20(committee)%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Emeetings%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20any%20community%20engagements%2C%20which%20results%20in%20their%20concerns%20not%20being%20addressed%20during%20the%20decision-making%20process.%20On%20average%2C%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20all%20vulnerable%20communities%20surveyed%20suggested%20that%20improvements%20from%20the%20government%20are%20needed%20in%20terms%20of%20health%2C%20sanitation%2C%20flood%20prevention%20infrastructure%20and%20other%20general%20infrastructure.%20As%20much%20as%2060%25%20of%20the%20population%20takes%20water%20from%20public%20wells%20and%20does%20not%20have%20access%20to%20water%20connections.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDense%20concrete%20and%20impermeable%20surfaces%2C%20taking%20the%20place%20of%20natural%20infrastructure%20like%20water%20bodies%2C%20green%20cover%20and%20open%20spaces%2C%20have%20also%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwri-india.org%2Fblog%2Fkerala-flooding-natural-calamity-or-manmade-disaster%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimpacted%20the%20ability%20of%20cities%20to%20manage%20water%20runoff%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20heavy%20and%20erratic%20rainfall%20patterns%2C%20resulting%20in%20devastating%20instances%20of%20flooding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThis%20is%20where%20nature-based%20solutions%20play%20an%20important%20role.%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Kochi%2C%20for%20example%2C%2012%20sites%20that%20are%20prone%20to%20flooding%20and%20dumping%20have%20been%20turned%20into%20urban%20forests%20through%20the%20Kochi%20Municipal%20Corporation%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wri-india.org%2Fblog%2Fkawaki-community-led-tree-based-intervention-climate-resilience-case-study%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKawaki%20initiative.%3C%2Fa%3E%20These%20erstwhile%20mosquito%20breeding%20grounds%20are%20now%20seeing%20the%20scientific%20plantation%20and%20maintenance%20of%20saplings%2C%20which%20as%20fully%20grown%20trees%20will%20offer%20much%20needed%20heat%20mitigation%20through%20green%20cover%20and%20permeable%20surfaces%20that%20can%20absorb%20rainfall%20and%20help%20recharge%20groundwater.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20municipal%20corporation%2C%20under%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.auegskerala.gov.in%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAyyankali%20Urban%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Scheme%20(AUEGS)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20trained%20over%20a%